  <div class="page">
    <p>Latency in LSM KVs</p>
    <p>oana.balmau@sydney.edu.au 6</p>
    <p>LSM KVs suffer from high tail latency spikes.</p>
    <p>Why is this important?  Cannot provide SLA guarantees to clients.</p>
    <p>Unpredictable performance when connecting LSM in larger pipelines.</p>
    <p>Latency spikes occur in write-dominated workloads.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="page">
    <p>oana.balmau@sydney.edu.au 7</p>
    <p>Solves latency spike problem for write-heavy workloads.</p>
    <p>SILK introduces the notion of an I/O scheduler for LSM KVs.</p>
    <p>No negative side-effects for other workloads.</p>
    <p>Our Contribution: The SILK LSM KV</p>
